{"type":"message","id":"e939d6e8","parentId":"79f87cd0","timestamp":"2026-02-22T02:30:30.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No email channel in the docs. Let me check the CLI reference for cron to understand how email delivery works.","thinkingSignature":"5fe3e96ee29f16d42bd0fcb3ff9af8b5a873979d688a3adfdd237e6397962d32"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rafojf8evy2j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/cli/cron.md | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":9647,"output":64,"cacheRead":11401,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21112,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771727427654}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1be8b87","parentId":"e939d6e8","timestamp":"2026-02-22T02:30:30.196Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rafojf8evy2j_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"CLI reference for `openclaw cron` (schedule and run background jobs)\"\nread_when:\n  - You want scheduled jobs and wakeups\n  - You’re debugging cron execution and logs\ntitle: \"cron\"\n---\n\n# `openclaw cron`\n\nManage cron jobs for the Gateway scheduler.\n\nRelated:\n\n- Cron jobs: [Cron jobs](/automation/cron-jobs)\n\nTip: run `openclaw cron --help` for the full command surface.\n\nNote: isolated `cron add` jobs default to `--announce` delivery. Use `--no-deliver` to keep\noutput internal. `--deliver` remains as a deprecated alias for `--announce`.\n\nNote: one-shot (`--at`) jobs delete after success by default. Use `--keep-after-run` to keep them.\n\nNote: recurring jobs now use exponential retry backoff after consecutive errors (30s → 1m → 5m → 15m → 60m), then return to normal schedule after the next successful run.\n\n## Common edits\n\nUpdate delivery settings without changing the message:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw cron edit <job-id> --announce --channel telegram --to \"123456789\"\n```\n\nDisable delivery for an isolated job:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw cron edit <job-id> --no-deliver\n```\n\nAnnounce to a specific channel:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw cron edit <job-id> --announce --channel slack --to \"channel:C1234567890\"\n```"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"---\nsummary: \"CLI reference for `openclaw cron` (schedule and run background jobs)\"\nread_when:\n  - You want scheduled jobs and wakeups\n  - You’re debugging cron execution and logs\ntitle: \"cron\"\n---\n\n# `openclaw cron`\n\nManage cron jobs for the Gateway scheduler.\n\nRelated:\n\n- Cron jobs: [Cron jobs](/automation/cron-jobs)\n\nTip: run `openclaw cron --help` for the full command surface.\n\nNote: isolated `cron add` jobs default to `--announce` delivery. Use `--no-deliver` to keep\noutput internal. `--deliver` remains as a deprecated alias for `--announce`.\n\nNote: one-shot (`--at`) jobs delete after success by default. Use `--keep-after-run` to keep them.\n\nNote: recurring jobs now use exponential retry backoff after consecutive errors (30s → 1m → 5m → 15m → 60m), then return to normal schedule after the next successful run.\n\n## Common edits\n\nUpdate delivery settings without changing the message:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw cron edit <job-id> --announce --channel telegram --to \"123456789\"\n```\n\nDisable delivery for an isolated job:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw cron edit <job-id> --no-deliver\n```\n\nAnnounce to a specific channel:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw cron edit <job-id> --announce --channel slack --to \"channel:C1234567890\"\n```","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771727430192}}
