{"type":"message","id":"d4ebdea6","parentId":"04e9b836","timestamp":"2026-02-22T02:30:41.697Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j2aawjol46kl_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"16:Each channel starts automatically when its config section exists (unless `enabled: false`).\n20:All channels support DM policies and group policies:\n36:`channels.defaults.groupPolicy` sets the default when a provider's `groupPolicy` is unset.\n37:Pairing codes expire after 1 hour. Pending DM pairing requests are capped at **3 per channel**.\n43:WhatsApp runs through the gateway's web channel (Baileys Web). It starts automatically when a linked session exists.\n47:  channels: {\n80:  channels: {\n96:- Per-account overrides: `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.sendReadReceipts`, `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.dmPolicy`, `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.allowFrom`.\n104:  channels: {\n156:- Bot token: `channels.telegram.botToken` or `channels.telegram.tokenFile`, with `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` as fallback for the default account.\n165:  channels: {\n183:        channelInfo: true,\n198:          channels: {\n230:- Token: `channels.discord.token`, with `DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN` as fallback for the default account.\n231:- Use `user:<id>` (DM) or `channel:<id>` (guild channel) for delivery targets; bare numeric IDs are rejected.\n232:- Guild slugs are lowercase with spaces replaced by `-`; channel keys use the slugged name (no `#`). Prefer guild IDs.\n235:- `channels.discord.ui.components.accentColor` sets the accent color for Discord components v2 containers.\n243:  channels: {\n276:  channels: {\n284:      channels: {\n301:        historyScope: \"thread\", // thread | channel\n328:- Use `user:<id>` (DM) or `channel:<id>` for delivery targets.\n332:**Thread session isolation:** `thread.historyScope` is per-thread (default) or shared across channel. `thread.inheritParent` copies parent channel transcript to new threads.\n348:  channels: {\n369:  channels: {\n387:  channels: {\n422:### Multi-account (all channels)\n424:Run multiple accounts per channel (each with its own `accountId`):\n428:  channels: {\n447:- Base channel settings apply to all accounts unless overridden per account."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"16:Each channel starts automatically when its config section exists (unless `enabled: false`).\n20:All channels support DM policies and group policies:\n36:`channels.defaults.groupPolicy` sets the default when a provider's `groupPolicy` is unset.\n37:Pairing codes expire after 1 hour. Pending DM pairing requests are capped at **3 per channel**.\n43:WhatsApp runs through the gateway's web channel (Baileys Web). It starts automatically when a linked session exists.\n47:  channels: {\n80:  channels: {\n96:- Per-account overrides: `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.sendReadReceipts`, `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.dmPolicy`, `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.allowFrom`.\n104:  channels: {\n156:- Bot token: `channels.telegram.botToken` or `channels.telegram.tokenFile`, with `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` as fallback for the default account.\n165:  channels: {\n183:        channelInfo: true,\n198:          channels: {\n230:- Token: `channels.discord.token`, with `DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN` as fallback for the default account.\n231:- Use `user:<id>` (DM) or `channel:<id>` (guild channel) for delivery targets; bare numeric IDs are rejected.\n232:- Guild slugs are lowercase with spaces replaced by `-`; channel keys use the slugged name (no `#`). Prefer guild IDs.\n235:- `channels.discord.ui.components.accentColor` sets the accent color for Discord components v2 containers.\n243:  channels: {\n276:  channels: {\n284:      channels: {\n301:        historyScope: \"thread\", // thread | channel\n328:- Use `user:<id>` (DM) or `channel:<id>` for delivery targets.\n332:**Thread session isolation:** `thread.historyScope` is per-thread (default) or shared across channel. `thread.inheritParent` copies parent channel transcript to new threads.\n348:  channels: {\n369:  channels: {\n387:  channels: {\n422:### Multi-account (all channels)\n424:Run multiple accounts per channel (each with its own `accountId`):\n428:  channels: {\n447:- Base channel settings apply to all accounts unless overridden per account.","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771727441693}}
{"type":"message","id":"b15829cf","parentId":"d4ebdea6","timestamp":"2026-02-22T02:30:46.955Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I don't see an email channel in the configuration reference. Let me check if there's a different way to configure it, or if email is handled differently.Actually, looking back at the cron logs, I noticed something - it says:\n```\n\"error\": \"Error: Telegram send failed: chat not found (chat_id=qn_home@163.com)\"\n```\n\nSo it's trying to send to Telegram with the chat_id being an email address, which doesn't work. And also it shows:\n```\n\"channel\": \"email\",\n\"from\": \"nohotnnn@gmail.com\",\n\"to\": \"qn_home@163.com\"\n```\n\nBut there's no email channel configured in OpenClaw. Let me check if there's a way to add email support via a plugin, or if we need to configure SMTP.Let me search for how to set up SMTP or email in OpenClaw.","thinkingSignature":"25479296e5590ab2ef1dc40151728e7b2644016e1b5dde1d3e04781619de5593"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iydm15t1y01x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"smtp\\|SMTP\" /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":11431,"output":229,"cacheRead":11401,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23061,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771727441697}}
